<div class="content" name="BYTE_SIZEDARR" uuid="e27714f4-6cfb-42c3-b4df-313c2b77a142"><p>The BYTE_SIZEDARR structure specifies a BYTE array.</p><dl>
<dd>
<div><pre> typedef struct _BYTE_SIZEDARR {
   unsigned long clSize;
   [size_is(clSize)] byte* pData;
 } BYTE_SIZEDARR;
</pre></div>
</dd></dl><p><b>clSize:</b>  MUST be set to the total
number of elements in the array. This MUST be nonzero.</p><p><b>pData:</b>  MUST be an array of BYTEs.</p><p>Data of this type MUST be marshaled as specified in <a href="https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=89824" data-linktype="external">[C706]</a> section 14,
with the exception that it MUST be marshaled by using a little-endian data
representation, regardless of the data representation format label. For more
information, see [C706] section 14.2.5.</p></div>